  "texts": [
    "Let y ij ∈ {0, 1} represent the true outcome of whether x i is higher ranked than x j, such that y ij = 1(s i > s j).",
    "Here, an LLM is used to model the probability that response i is better than response j, p ij,",
    "Which can alternatively be converted into hard decisions, ŷij, by selecting the most likely outcome.",
    "Let C = {c k } k=1...R represent a set of comparisons, where R is the total number of comparisons, and each comparison c = (i, j) indicates the indices of the two considered candidate responses.",
    "For example, the set of all possible comparisons, C = {(i, j) | i, j ∈ [1...N ], i ̸ = j}, could be used, or alternatively a smaller subset of comparisons."
  ],
